
@startuml

class User {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +email: String
  +dateOfBirth: Date
}

class Account {
  +accountNumber: String
  +type: String
  +user: User
}

class PersonalAccount extends Account {
  +canSendFriendRequests: Boolean
  +canReceiveFriendRequests: Boolean
}

class BusinessAccount extends Account {
  +companyName: String
  +monthlyFee: Double
}

class Page {
  +name: String
  +visitCount: Integer
  +account: Account
}

class AdvertisementPage extends Page {
  +bounceRate: Double
  +clickThroughRate: Double
  +conversionRate: Double
}

User "1" -- "1" Account : has
Account "1" -- "0..*" Page : creates
PersonalAccount "1" -- "0..*" Page : can manage
BusinessAccount "1" -- "0..*" AdvertisementPage : can create

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:

- **User → Account**: A user has exactly one account (1:1).
- **Account → Page**: An account can create multiple pages (1:*).
- **PersonalAccount → Page**: A personal account can be granted privileges to manage pages created by other personal accounts.
- **BusinessAccount → AdvertisementPage**: A business account can create advertisement pages (special type of page).

